  "title": "⌚ Luxury Watch Technician/Watchmaker – High-End Timepieces | Up to $4200 + AWS",
  "description": "<p><strong>⌚ Luxury Watch Technician/Watchmaker – High-End Timepieces | Up to $4200 + AWS</strong></p><p>Employment Type: Full Time, Permanent</p><p>Salary: $3800 to $4200 + AWS</p><p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>We are seeking a skilled and meticulous Luxury Watchmaker(Horologist) to service, repair, and maintain high-end mechanical andquartz timepieces. This role is ideal for an experienced professional who takes pride in precision craftsmanship and working with luxury watch brands.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Diagnose, service, and repair luxury mechanical and quartz watches</li><li>Perform complete overhauls, movement assembly, and adjustments</li><li>Conduct water-resistance testing and quality control checks</li><li>Ensure all repairs meet brand and service-centre standards</li><li>Maintain detailed service records and documentation</li><li>Handle luxury watches with care, professionalism, and confidentiality</li><li>Support after-sales service operations and technical consultations</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Formal training or certification in watchmaking / horology preferred</li><li>Proven experience servicing luxury or high-end timepieces</li><li>Strong understanding of mechanical and quartz movements</li><li>High attention to detail and precision workmanship</li><li>Able to work independently and meet service timelines</li><li>Familiarity with brand service standards is an advantage</li></ul><p><strong>Why Join Us</strong></p><ul><li>Work with prestigious luxury watch brands</li><li>Professional workshop environment with high technical standards</li><li>Stable role with long-term career growth</li><li>Opportunity to further develop technical expertise in horology</li></ul><p><strong>Apply Now!</strong><br />If you are passionate about fine watchmaking and precision craftsmanship, we’d love to hear from you.</p><p>Send your resume to: <a href=\"mailto:Vanessa.chua@crew.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Vanessa.chua@crew.sg</a></p><p>Please include your <strong>availability, notice period, expected salary.</strong></p><p><em>* Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</em></p><p>Vanessa Chua Peng Teng (R25158315)</p><p>Associate Consultant</p><p>HRnet Ventures Pte Ltd - CREW by HRnet</p><p>E.A. 24C2435</p>",
